   <body>
      <context>You can organize project and contract documents into folders created in the document management system.<note>Based on the roles and permissions defined, the stakeholders can  create a new folder to the pre-defined folder structure.</note>
      </context>
      <ol>
         <li href="../../../Warehouse/Task_Warehouse/AcsPrjContDocsNav.dita#task-5739/AccProContDocFolder">
            <p/>
         </li>
         <li>
            <p>Click<uicontrol>New</uicontrol>. <image href="../../Icons/NewFolder.png" placement="inline">
                  <alt>New</alt>
               </image>
            </p>
            <p>The<uicontrol>New Folder</uicontrol> dialog box is displayed.</p>
            <p>
               <fig>
                  <title>New Folder</title>
                  <image href="../../Icons/Screenshots_Icons/New_Folder.jpg" placement="inline"/>
               </fig>
            </p>
         </li>
         <li>
            <p>In the<uicontrol>Name</uicontrol> box, type the folder name.</p>
         </li>
         <li>
            <p>In the<uicontrol>Description</uicontrol> box, type a brief description of the folder.</p>
         </li>
         <li>
            <p>Ensure the<uicontrol>Inherit Parent Permissions</uicontrol> check box is selected to provide the same permissions to the folder as its parent folder.</p>
            <p>Optionally, clear the check box to provide permissions to the folder as defined for the roles of the current user.<note>  If the folder is being created for a project, then the permissions are inherited only for the roles that the user is invited to in the project. </note>
            </p>
         </li>
         <li>
            <p>Click<uicontrol>Save</uicontrol>.</p>
            <p>The folder is created in the selected folder.</p>
         </li>
      </ol>
